<TITLE> Accident kills medicine rep </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Kushtia, May 22 (bdnews24.com)A medical representative was killed in a road accident in Kushtia on Saturday. The deceased was identified as Abul Bashar, 32, a sales representative of Renata Medicine Company, of Goalgram area of Daulatpur upazila in Kushtia. Kushtia Sadr police chief Asaduzzaman told bdnews24.com that Bashar was on his way to supply medicine riding a motor cycle when a bus ran him over at Chargopalpur on the Kushtia-Panti Highway at around 9.30am. Asaduzzaman said that Bashar died on the spot. The body was sent to the Kushtia General Hospital for autopsy. The bus could not be seized. A case has been filed with the police station. bdnew
